I got irritated by the fact, that the addition of the `@ConstructorProperties` annotation is not consistent.

```
// Class gets @ConstructorProperties annotation
@Value public class TestClass {
    private final double foo;
}

// Class has *no* @ConstructorProperties annotation
@Builder @Value public class TestClass {
    private final double foo;
}

// Class gets @ConstructorProperties annotation
@AllArgsConstructor @Builder @Value public class TestClass {
    private final double foo;
}
```

In my opinion this is irritating behaviour. Why is the `@ConstructorProperties` annotation removed when there is a `@Builder` annotation but no `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation? If the reason is, that with a `@Builder` the constructors are not meant to be used by the user, than they better should be declared private. At least I propose that the documentation should be clarified. All I have found there is that lombok would by default add this annotation to all constructors with at least one argument.

